Carl N. Singer was named chairman of this communications and electronics equipment supplier, succeeding Louis H. Wolcott, who resigned from the board.
Mr. Singer will continue in his current positions as chairman of Miami-based Fundamental Management Corp., Microdyne's largest stockholder, and chairman of Mineola, N.Y.-based Robeson Industries Corp. Robert P. Adelman, former president and chief executive officer of Rogers Group, was named to the Microdyne board slot vacated by Mr. Wolcott, who will continue with Microdyne as an assistant to the president. 

